race.comment: GREAT FUEGO (9) was awful on heavy ground at Stony Creek over 1100m last time out. Can forgive that run and the effort at Kyneton prior has her in the finish. Key runner. BRICKENDON (15) drew a poor gate on debut last start over 1114m at Geelong and finished 5 lengths from the winner in fifth. Jett Stanley is aboard again. Better for the race experience and has the ability to make his mark. PETE THE PROPHET (17) was well in the market on debut last start but could only manage seventh over 1009m at Yarra Valley. Has placed since then in a Caulfield Heath trial. Expecting a strong run in this field. STORMING CAMELOT (8) Stephen V Brown gelding making his first race start. Trialled two times to prepare for this with mixed results. Watch for any market confidence.
